[{"id":"VR737502","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a box on a horizontal surface connected by a spring on its left side to a wall. There are 3 positions indicated from left to right. Position Q is located closest to the wall. Position R is located a distance of x to the right of Position Q and is at the left edge of the box. Position S is located furthest to right and is a distance of x halves to the right of Position R. A block which is smaller than the box is held at a very small heightÂ above the box.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR737502.g03.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A spring has its left end fixed to a wall and its right end attached to a box, which can move back and forth on a horizontal surface with negligible friction, as shown in the figure. When the spring is at its relaxed length the box is at position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>R</mtext></math></span></span>. The spring is compressed a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi></math></span></span> from its relaxed length and the box is then released from rest at position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\"><math alttext=\"Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>Q</mtext></math></span></span>. The box moves from position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\"><math alttext=\"Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>Q</mtext></math></span></span> to position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>R</mtext></math></span></span>, continues moving on to position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"S\"><math alttext=\"S\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>S</mtext></math></span></span> a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction x over 2, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"the fraction x over 2, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span> to the right of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>R</mtext></math></span></span>, and continues moving beyond position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"S\"><math alttext=\"S\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>S</mtext></math></span></span> toward the right. As the box moves, a block can be dropped onto the box from a small height just above the box. When this happens, the block sticks to the box in a perfectly inelastic collision and the two objects move together horizontally after colliding. At which labeled position(s) can the block be dropped onto the box so that the block-box system's total momentum and total kinetic energy are each the same immediately before and immediately after the collision? Neglect the block's vertical component of motion, and treat the collision as occurring instantaneously.</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR737502_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">At position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\"><math alttext=\"Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>Q</mtext></math></span></span> only</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">At position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>R</mtext></math></span></span> only</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">At position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"S\"><math alttext=\"S\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>S</mtext></math></span></span> only</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">At positions <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\"><math alttext=\"Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>Q</mtext></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>R</mtext></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"S\"><math alttext=\"S\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>S</mtext></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":0}]